<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF8EFF9DFF7EF9B7FCC4F99C" box="[136,819,1634,1660]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8EFF9DFF7EF9B7FCC4F99C" blockId="15.[136,1452,1634,2056]" box="[136,819,1634,1660]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8EFF9DFF7EF9B7FEE4F99C" bold="true" box="[136,275,1634,1660]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">Etymology:</emphasis>
—Named for the dark brown, almost black fruit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF8EFF9DFF4BF950FCCFF8EC" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8EFF9DFF4BF950FCCFF8EC" blockId="15.[136,1452,1634,2056]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8EFF9DFF4BF950FECDF97F" bold="true" box="[189,314,1669,1695]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8EFF9DFEA0F953FE2AF940" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[342,477,1670,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuliginea">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8EFF9DFEA0F953FE2AF940" box="[342,477,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">C. fuliginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8EFF9DFC88F953FBA6F940" box="[894,1105,1670,1696]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8EFF9DFC88F953FC00F940" box="[894,1015,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the fully-formed, lingulate lower leaves which are not fleshy, combined with the blackish mature fruit which are more than 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFB49F97FFB08F924" box="[1215,1279,1706,1732]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
high and wide. It most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8EFF9DFE5CF91BFC51F908" authority="Lansdown and Hassemer (2021)" authorityName="Lansdown and Hassemer" authorityYear="2021" box="[426,934,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ecarinata">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8EFF9DFE5CF91BFDC2F908" box="[426,565,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">C. ecarinata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF8EFF9DFDCAF91BFC51F908" author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Hassemer, G." box="[572,934,1742,1768]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" pagination="85 - 118" refId="ref33574" refString="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Hassemer, G. (2021) The genus Callitriche in south America. Phytotaxa 501 (1): 85 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 501.1.3" type="journal article" year="2021">Lansdown and Hassemer (2021)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from which it can be distinguished by its long lingulate leaves, solitary flowers and the larger blackish fruit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF8EFF82FF4BF8C0FE41FEA8" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="259" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" type="description">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8EFF9DFF4BF8C0FAB0F804" blockId="15.[136,1452,1634,2056]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8EFF9DFF4BF8C0FEA6F8CF" bold="true" box="[189,337,1813,1839]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">Description:</emphasis>
—Stem and leaf scales present. Leaf bases connate. Lingulate leaves 5.0– 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFB73F8C3FB11F8D0" box="[1157,1254,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.28" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="12.8">12.8 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFACCF8C3FA5BF8D0" box="[1338,1452,1814,1840]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.0">1–1.8 mm</quantity>
wide; expanded floating or submerged leaves 2.0– 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFD4DF8EFFCE6F8B4" box="[699,785,1850,1877]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
long × 1.5–4.0 mm wide; venation simple with a few loops outside and occasionally within the secondary veins, petiole 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFCE9F88BFC8DF898" box="[799,890,1886,1912]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="1.0">1–7 mm</quantity>
long; leaves of terrestrial plants unknown. Flowers solitary. Bracts caducous, very narrow, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFDB6F857FD62F87C" box="[576,661,1922,1948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long. Styles erect, persistent 2.0– 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFBF8F857FB94F87C" box="[1038,1123,1922,1948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
long. Filament erect, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFAA1F857FF43F820" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="1.9" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2.3 mm</quantity>
long; anthers 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFEA2F873FE2BF820" box="[340,476,1958,1984]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.4 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFDC5F873FD4CF820" box="[563,699,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
wide, number of locules unknown; pollen yellow. Fruit subsessile, not strumose, slightly wider than long, black when mature, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFCD4F81FFC5EF804" box="[802,937,1994,2020]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.3 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8EFF9DFC09F81FFB71F804" box="[1023,1158,1994,2021]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="258" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide, unwinged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8EFF9DFF4BF838FE32F7E8" blockId="15.[136,1452,1634,2056]" box="[189,453,2029,2056]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8EFF9DFF4BF838FEAEF7E7" bold="true" box="[189,345,2029,2055]" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">Illustrations:</emphasis>
— 
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF8EFF9DFE81F83BFE36F7E8" box="[375,449,2030,2056]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,225,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-31@4.[151,1436,190,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Fruits of Callitriche in Oceania and Australasia: a—C. antarctica, b—C. aucklandica, c—C. brachycarpa, d—C. brutia, e—C. capricorni, f—C. chathamensis, g—C. cyclocarpa i face on and ii end on, h—C. cycloptera, i—C. deflexa, j—C. fuliginea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577540/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="258">Fig. 1j</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BFF4BFE41FEA8" blockId="16.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BFF4BFEA1FF58" bold="true" box="[189,342,158,184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FE84FF4AFE04FF58" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[370,499,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuliginea">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FE84FF4AFE04FF58" box="[370,499,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C.fuliginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FC87FF4BFBC8FF58" box="[881,1087,158,184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FC87FF4BFC1DFF58" box="[881,1002,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region except 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FAEAFF4AFA5CFF58" box="[1308,1451,159,185]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Deschampsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antarctica">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FAEAFF4AFA5CFF58" box="[1308,1451,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. antarctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FF4EFF16FE91FF3C" authorityName="Pursh" authorityYear="1814" box="[184,358,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4EFF16FE91FF3C" box="[184,358,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its large unwinged, blackish fruit. 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FCE4FF16FC51FF3C" box="[786,934,195,221]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Deschampsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antarctica">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FCE4FF16FC51FF3C" box="[786,934,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. antarctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in its fleshy leaves, compared to those of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FF5EFF32FED9FEE0" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[168,302,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuliginea">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF5EFF32FED9FEE0" box="[168,302,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. fuliginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of which the leaves are thin and delicate. 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FCE7FF32FC37FEE0" authorityName="Pursh" authorityYear="1814" box="[785,960,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FCE7FF32FC37FEE0" box="[785,960,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
typically has smaller and characteristically isodiametric fruit. 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FEAEFEDEFE2CFEC4" authorityName="von Linne" authorityYear="1753" box="[344,475,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FEAEFEDEFE2CFEC4" box="[344,475,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be considered similar, but at least within the region, always has at least a narrow wing at the top of the fruit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF91FF82FF4BFE87FEA7FD88" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BFE87FCD5FE70" blockId="16.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BFE87FEAEFE8C" bold="true" box="[189,345,338,364]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Native. 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FE38FE86FDA5FE8C" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[462,594,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuliginea">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FE38FE86FDA5FE8C" box="[462,594,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. fuliginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to New 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF91FF82FCC7FE87FC72FE8C" box="[817,901,338,364]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, where it is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="0061D1D4FF91FF82FB08FE87FA97FE8C" box="[1278,1376,338,364]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">holotype</typeStatus>
which was collected on Mount Salawaket, on the Huon Peninsula.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BFE4FFB29FE55" blockId="16.[136,1452,158,617]" box="[189,1246,410,437]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BFE4FFE30FE54" bold="true" box="[189,455,410,436]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Habitats and Ecology:</emphasis>
—Shallow water of boggy pool in alpine grassland. Elevation 
<quantity id="1822C293FF91FF82FB74FE4FFB2DFE55" box="[1154,1242,410,437]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9899999999999998" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" unit="m" value="2990.0">2990 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BFE6BFCA2FE1C" blockId="16.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BFE6BFE4FFE38" bold="true" box="[189,440,446,472]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
—The information available is not adequate to assess the conservation status of the species and it is therefore classed as Data Deficient (DD) (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF91FF82FD49FE37FCBEFE1C" author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[703,841,482,508]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" refId="ref32363" refString="IUCN (2012). IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. 2 nd ed. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK. 32 pp" type="book" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BFDD3FEA7FD88" blockId="16.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BFDD3FEFEFDC0" bold="true" box="[189,265,518,544]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FED0FDD2FE5EFDC0" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[294,425,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuliginea">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FED0FDD2FE5EFDC0" box="[294,425,518,545]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. fuliginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely poorly known, the only specimens seen are both from the same gathering made in 1963. There is an urgent need to survey upland areas of New 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF91FF82FCAEFDFFFC5EFDA4" box="[856,937,554,580]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Guinea</collectingCountry>
to establish whether it persists and whether it occurs elsewhere.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
